  <summary date="2017-12-04T05:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">This bill requires the President to establish a commission called the "Anti-Bullying Roundtable" to study bullying in&#160;elementary and secondary schools in the United States.

The roundtable must submit a report about best practices concerning bullying, including recommendations for: (1)&#160;combating bullying, (2) educating school officials to recognize bullying, and (3) helping parents to address the early warning signs of bullying with their children.</summary>
